content:
Financial Services Cloud users can use this version of the Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) to view preconfigured relationship graphs. Add the ARC Financial Services Cloud component to record pages to let your users see both Financial Services Cloud relationships and related list relationships in one view on Account records.

Note: This is a view-only version of ARC, for instructions on using the new version, see Create and View Custom ARC Relationship Graphs.

To view an ARC graph, users must have read access to the fields on the Contact, Account, Reciprocal Role, Account-Contact Relationship, Account-Account Relationship, and Contact-Contact Relationship objects.

Add the component for Actionable Relationship Center to page layouts where your users need it.

Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) displays different kinds of account and contact relationships in one convenient interface.

Help users manage related records in Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) by configuring the related lists that they see.

The Actionable Relationship Center (ARC) interface lets you create, edit, and remove account-account and account-contact relationships.

Considerations for implementing Actionable Relationship Center (Original ARC):

* ARC is supported for orgs with the Person account Model.
* ARC isn't supported for orgs using the Individual Model.
* ARC requires active picklist values on the Association Type field of the Account-Account Relationship object.
title: Actionable Relationship Center for Financial Services Cloud
